What is the 20th digit after the decimal point of the sum of the decimal equivalents for the fractions $ rac{1}{7}$ and $ rac{1}{3}$? ||| The decimal representation of \( rac{1}{7}\) is approximately \(0.142857\) and for \( rac{1}{3}\), it is approximately \(0.33\). Adding these, we get:
 egin{align*}
