&= 30^{\circ}.
\end{align*}Since $AB$ is parallel to $DC,$ we have $$\angle ACD = \angle BAC = 30^{\circ}$$due to alternate angles. In $\triangle ADC,$ \begin{align*}
\angle DAC &= 180^{\circ}-\angle ADC - \angle ACD \\
&= 180^{\circ}-115^{\circ}-30^{\circ} \\
