We can then subtract GAE directly from 360 degrees, so we have 
\[ 
360^\circ - 120^\circ = 240^\circ. 
\] Maybe that leads us to the fact that reflex angle might represent something conventionally wrong. Now if we fill in the semi-angle we thought we had originally, we get a confounding math problem and rumble it into something easy: \( x = 240 \circ \). Hence, \( x = \boxed{240} \).

