[/asy] ||| If the diameter of the small circle is 2, then the radius is 1. The radius of the larger circle is then 8 because 4 times the radius of the small circle is 4 times 2. The area of the larger circle is \pi8^2 = 64\pi and the area of the smaller circle is \pi1^2 = 1\pi. Then the gray area is 64\pi - 1\pi = 63\pi. So, the area of the gray region is \boxed{63\pi} sq units.

